{
  "texts": [
    "Inclusion should go beyond the provision of \"lowresource\" methods (Gururangan et al., 2022), i.e., framing the under-representation of social minorities as a data scarcity problem.",
    "Instead, it should account for preventive considerations that respond to diverse human needs and preferences.",
    "x Multi-stakeholders participatory design and human-centered AI can be a valid alternative to technological solutionism.",
    "(Multi-stakeholder participatory design, Prioritizing Human-centric AI) x Intersectionality requires special attention and specific methods to account for the interplay of the different (protected) attributes.",
    "(Intersectionality) x A principled way of tackling bias is to rely on causal reasoning."
  ]
}